rComments: Prof. Downar exudes passion throughout the course, as he often gets philosophical and ties it all to the bigger picture making his lectures truly inspirational. I was also worried about the neuroscience aspect but it was quite straightforward. Posts videos online so attendance is up to you. Unavailable outside lectures, which can be a hindrance.

Downar is an excellent lecturer. His class is fascinating, and he encourages discussion (often going broad, from brain to philosophy). Lot of info but clear. If you do not have a neuroscience background, get ready to learn a lot of neuroanatomy. There are bell ringers. He posts lecture slides/videos. Con: Not very accessible outside of class.
He was fantastic. His passion for rTMS was contagious. I thought the course would be too hard since I do not have a neuroscience background, but it was very doable.
Goes into long-winded discussions on supplementary topics. Grade acquisition is straightforward. Unavailable,  practices benign indifference, discourages more in-depth interest in topics.
